header.gameNote: FRESNO STATE TOURNAMENT AT FRESNO CA

article.headline: South Alabama 67, UC-Irvine 63
article.story: FRESNO, Calif. (AP) -- Demetric Bennett scored 27 points and Daon Merritt added 18 to lead South Alabama to a 67-63 season-opening victory over UC Irvine. Adam Templeton finished with a team-high 17 points and five rebounds for UC Irvine before fouling out. The Anteaters had a chance to tie the game at the end of regulation, but Merritt stole the ball from Marcus McIntosh near midcourt and drew an intentional foul with two seconds left. Merritt made both free throws to ice the game. After poor shooting during the first half, South Alabama shot 56 percent in the second. The Jaguars made 11 of 25 three-pointers, including a 6-of-9 effort from Bennett. South Alabama led by as many as seven points in the first half before the Anteaters rallied to force a 23-23 halftime tie. Merritt added seven assists for South Alabama, and Brandon Davis had five steals. Patrick Sanders had 11 points for UC Irvine. Darren Fells and McIntosh added 10 each.
